  ${
    $d f k m x z F $.  $d f k m n z ph $.  $d f k m x z R $.  $d f k m x z X $.
    $d x y z A $.  $d k m n S $.
    supcvg.1 $e |- X e. _V $.
    supcvg.2 $e |- S = sup ( A , RR , < ) $.
    supcvg.3 $e |- R = ( n e. NN |-> ( S - ( 1 / n ) ) ) $.
    supcvg.4 $e |- ( ph -> X =/= (/) ) $.
    supcvg.5 $e |- ( ph -> F : X -onto-> A ) $.
    supcvg.6 $e |- ( ph -> A C_ RR ) $.
    supcvg.7 $e |- ( ph -> E. x e. RR A. y e. A y <_ x ) $.
    $( Extract a sequence ` f ` in ` X ` such that the image of the points in
       the bounded set ` A ` converges to the supremum ` S ` of the set.
       Similar to Equation 4 of [Kreyszig] p. 144.  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 15-Feb-2013.)  (The proof was shortened by Mario Carneiro,
       26-Apr-2014.) $)
    supcvg $p |- ( ph -> E. f ( f : NN --> X /\ ( F o. f ) ~~> S ) ) $=
      ( cn wcel cr vk vz vm cv wf cfv cle wbr wral wa wex ccom cli wrex csup c1
      clt cdiv cmin wceq oveq2 oveq2d ovex fvmpt adantl crp wss wne w3a wfo fof
      syl feq3 syl5ibcom f00 simprbi syl6 necon3d mpd 3jca suprcl syl5eqel nnrp
      co rpreccl ltsubrp syl2an eqbrtrd syl6breq adantr nnrecre resubcl ffvelrn
      c0 wb fmptd sylan suprlub syl2anc mpbid sselda ltle reximdva forn rexeqdv
      wi crn wfn ffn breq2 rexrn bitr3d ralrimiva nnenom fveq2 breq2d axcc4 cvv
