  ${
    $d k n $.  $d j k F $.  $d j k H $.
    harmonic.1 $e |- F = ( n e. NN |-> ( 1 / n ) ) $.
    harmonic.2 $e |- H = seq 1 ( + , F ) $.
    $( The harmonic series ` H ` diverges.  This fact follows from the stronger
       ~ emcl , which establishes that the harmonic series grows as
       ` log n + gamma + ` _o_(1), but this uses a more elementary method,
       attributed to Nicole Oresme (1323-1382).  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 11-Jul-2014.) $)
    harmonic $p |- -. H e. dom ~~> $=
      ( vk wcel cn0 c1 wbr cn cr cc0 wceq adantl cdiv co cle syl cmul vj cli cv
      cdm csu clt wrex csn cxp nn0uz cz 0z a1i cfv 1z elexi fvconst2 caddc cseq
      1re eleq1i biimpi oveq2 ovex fvmpt nnrecre eqeltrd crp nnrp rpreccl rpge0
      wa 3syl breqtrrd nnre lep1 nngt0 peano2re peano2nn lerec syl22anc 3brtr4d
      wb mpbid c2 cexp fveq2d oveq12d cmpt fconstmpt 2nn nnexpcl mpan oveq2d cc
      wne nncn nnne0 recid syl2anc eqtrd mpteq2ia eqtr4i climcnds isumrecl arch
      cfz chash cfn fzfid ax-1cn fsumconst sylancl hashfz1 oveq1d mulid1 3eqtrd
      wn nnnn0 wss elfznn ssriv 0re lt01 ltleii isumless eqbrtrrd lenlt syl2anr
